trans-unit.target: Overlooking the Grand Canal , just a few meters from the Rialto Bridge , La Porta d'Acqua offers Mediterranean cuisine inspired by Neapolitan and Venetian traditions and fish from the nearby fish market. The intimate room on the first floor can be reserved for special events .

trans-unit.target: La Porta d'Acqua is a guarantee. Well-known by Venetians and non-Venetians alike, this splendid establishment of Venetian dining has now moved just a few meters to gain an incredible view of the Grand Canal . Overlooking Riva del Vin, a few meters from the Rialto Bridge , the restaurant is housed in a finely restored 15th-century building with contemporary taste. From the beautiful interior rooms (one on the first floor, also available for events , private parties, business dinners) to the magnificent outdoor area, and the stunning garden where you can enjoy an aperitif at the cocktail bar , every detail of this place has been meticulously thought out. Easily accessible from any direction, La Porta d'Acqua successfully combines the quality of its dishes with a decidedly extraordinary location.

trans-unit.target: At the entrance of the venue, a spacious counter leads to a pleasant bar area that encompasses two equally appealing aspects: a tasty bacaro from morning until early afternoon; a refined cocktail bar with signature cocktails and enticing revisited spritzes created by the skilled hands of the bartender. The perfect place to enjoy delicious cicchetti and crostini and to complete your magnificent dinner with an original aperitif or a well-crafted digestif.

trans-unit.target: Venice has always been a meeting point of various cultures and peoples . The idea behind our dishes is to combine tradition with innovation, respecting the seasonality of the ingredients. A successful blend of Mediterranean recipes with classic Venetian dishes . The cuisine ranges from a wide selection of daily catches , selected meats and vegetables from the lagoon islands. All accompanied by the best Italian wines with a selection from small winemakers' cellars . Stop by the bar for a cicchetto at lunch or for a cocktail and a revisited spritz in the evening.
